    <h2>Admission</h2>
    <p>At our nursery and primary school, we have a thorough admission process to ensure that every child is given the opportunity to thrive in our community. Here are some of the attributes that we consider during the admission process:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Age eligibility - We accept children who are between the ages of 2 and 5 for our nursery program, and between the ages of 5 and 11 for our primary school program.</li>
      <li>Academic background - We consider the academic history of the child, and request transcripts or report cards from their previous school if applicable.</li>
      <li>Interview - We conduct interviews with both the child and their parents/guardians to better understand their background, interests, and goals.</li>
      <li>Health and development - We require a health check-up to ensure that the child is physically and mentally fit for our school environment.</li>
      <li>Diversity - We value diversity and seek to create a welcoming and inclusive environment for all students, regardless of their race, ethnicity, religion, or socioeconomic background.</li>
      <li>Availability of space - We have limited availability and admission is based on a first-come, first-served basis.</li>
    </ul>
